@Teemu Well, tell me what you get here (and no, French isn't the only situation where this can happen, but after the U.S., they are the ones most likely to not conform to so-called international standards): `SET LANGUAGE FRENCH; 
 DECLARE @d DATETIME = '2016-03-07';
 SELECT DATEPART(MONTH, @d);`. I've been preaching about this for years, but people still get surprised by it. [This article I wrote in 2009](http://sqlblog.com/blogs/aaron_bertrand/archive/2009/10/16/bad-habits-to-kick-mishandling-date-range-queries.aspx)...
